						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up in front of Narasiṁha temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 134[7], Krōdhi, Śrāvaṇa, śu. 11.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Mentions a certain artisan Irugana Ōbaḷa-Nāyaka who died, when he is doing polishing work <hi rend="italic">(varukuṁpani)</hi> in the temple of Narasiṁha.</p>						

